doc.after: Kilkenny GAA, the Kilkenny County Board of the Gaelic Athletic Association (Kilkenny GAA) (Irish: Cumann LÃºthchleas Gael Coiste Cill Channaigh) is one of the 32 county boards of the GAA in Ireland and is responsible for Gaelic Games in County Kilkenny. The county board has its head office and main grounds at Nowlan Park and is also responsible for Kilkenny inter-county teams in all codes at all levels. The Kilkenny branch of the Gaelic Athletic Association was founded in 1887.
